Subject: Re: [T2] valve adjustment

Jeremiah Stutte wrote:
> this engine has under 4,000 miles since she was rebuilt.  is it common
> for the valves to tighten up following a rebuild?

you really need to do another valve job so you can note the trend.  So, 
at your next adjustment, if you have tight valves, it means your valves 
are stretching or the seats are sinking.  Both are indicative of high 
head temps, which definitely needs to be addressed or you will have 
problems.
